So if you do anything bad,

261
00:14:18,083 --> 00:14:20,875
it can be used to track you
down, and bring you to justice.

262
00:14:22,958 --> 00:14:25,708
And until we can identify
them as the same person,

263
00:14:25,791 --> 00:14:28,166
we can't accuse them
of wrong-doing.

264
00:14:28,250 --> 00:14:29,166
[PIROSHIKI]
I'm betting our perp

265
00:14:29,250 --> 00:14:30,833
normally plays the
game from home,

266
00:14:30,916 --> 00:14:33,208
but when he's account hacking,
or other illegal stuff,

267
00:14:33,291 --> 00:14:35,333
he uses a different IP.

268
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:38,333
So what? We're just
supposed to take it?

269
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:40,666
[BLACK MAGICIAN] That option
isn't acceptable either.

270
00:14:40,750 --> 00:14:41,833
Sorry to intrude.

271
00:14:41,916 --> 00:14:43,375
[PIROSHIKI]
The Black Magician!

272
00:14:43,458 --> 00:14:44,375
[BLACK MAGICIAN]
I came across something

273
00:14:44,458 --> 00:14:46,416
I found rather disturbing.

274
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:49,375
You should take a
look at this URL.

275
00:14:55,416 --> 00:14:57,375
"LON's Scam Blog-stravaganza?"

276
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:58,791
What is this crap?

277
00:14:58,875 --> 00:15:00,375
[BLACK MAGICIAN] It's the
blog of a famous swindler

278
00:15:00,458 --> 00:15:03,333
known for running scams
across multiple games.

279
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:04,958
In fact, his most recent post

280
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,750
jokes about how he
hacked your account.

281
00:15:06,833 --> 00:15:08,208
Damn it!

282
00:15:08,291 --> 00:15:10,166
We've gotta do what it takes
to make that A$$ face pay!

283
00:15:10,250 --> 00:15:13,083
If I get the chance, I'll smash
the SH@# out of that guy!

284
00:15:13,166 --> 00:15:15,708
Whoa, the chat window
isn't displaying those words.

285
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:16,958
If you ask me,

286
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:19,958
this guy's a real
F@#K-WIT A$$-GOBBLER.

287
00:15:20,041 --> 00:15:21,291
[PIROSHIKI gasps]

288
00:15:21,375 --> 00:15:24,458
He's a moronic miscreant
with a desire to show off.

289
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:26,541
He can't keep from
bragging about it.

290
00:15:26,625 --> 00:15:28,291
The internet is full
of dorks like him.

291
00:15:28,375 --> 00:15:29,458
And that's not all.

292
00:15:29,541 --> 00:15:32,041
He also dabbles in
RMT's from time to time.

293
00:15:32,125 --> 00:15:33,583
Though he must cover
his tracks well,

294
00:15:33,666 --> 00:15:35,958
since he hasn't been
caught in the act yet.

295
00:15:36,041 --> 00:15:37,833
What's a RMT?

296
00:15:37,916 --> 00:15:40,291
[AKANE] You don't know
what that is either?

297
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:42,416
[KYOH]
Real money trades.

298
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:44,958
People sell off rare,
in-game items,

299
00:15:45,041 --> 00:15:47,791
but for real life currencies,
instead of gil.

300
00:15:47,875 --> 00:15:49,958
It's against the terms
of service in <i>LA</i> .

301
00:15:50,041 --> 00:15:51,208
That's it!

302
00:15:51,291 --> 00:15:53,500
It sounds like someone
just had an epiphany.

303
00:15:53,583 --> 00:15:55,875
There's no guarantee
that it's gonna work,

304
00:15:55,958 --> 00:15:57,708
but at least it will give us
a chance to take down

305
00:15:57,791 --> 00:15:59,708
that swindling butt-munch!

306
00:16:09,291 --> 00:16:12,375
[AKANE] Nishimura's plan has
us going through the night.

307
00:16:12,458 --> 00:16:16,333
If this doesn't work, that
idiot better say his prayers.

308
00:16:16,416 --> 00:16:20,166
[HIDEKI] So freaking tired.
Three days with no sleep.

309
00:16:20,250 --> 00:16:23,041
Not to mention, I think my
stomach's eating itself.

310
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:24,041
[doorbell rings]

311
00:16:24,125 --> 00:16:26,166
Doorbell, or am I hallucinating?

312
00:16:26,250 --> 00:16:28,833
[doorbell ringing]

313
00:16:28,916 --> 00:16:31,750
[HIDEKI]
Yeah, yeah. I'm coming!

314
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:36,541
[giggles]

315
00:16:36,625 --> 00:16:38,291
I just dropped by--

316
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:41,625
Rusian, it's me,
your doting wife!

317
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:43,916
Geez, what was with
the harsh treatment?

318
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:46,125
I'm sorry. It was just a reflex.

319
00:16:46,208 --> 00:16:48,916
I expected a significantly
warmer welcome.

320
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,833
It is the first time your wife
has visited your family home.

321
00:16:51,916 --> 00:16:56,000
Well, technically speaking,
you're not my wife anymore.

322
00:16:56,083 --> 00:16:58,375
Think about it. From the
moment Rusian was deleted,

323
00:16:58,458 --> 00:17:00,458
it officially annulled
our marriage.

324
00:17:00,541 --> 00:17:01,416
[gasps]

325
00:17:01,500 --> 00:17:03,666
So we're divorced?!

326
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:06,125
Are you really just
now realizing that?

327
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:08,458
Rusian's disappearance
was such a shock.

328
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:10,458
I can't believe
he's really gone.

329
00:17:10,541 --> 00:17:12,583
How could that phony Rusian
do something like this

330
00:17:12,666 --> 00:17:14,208
to such a sweet, tender heart?!

331
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:16,833
What kind of maniac are
we dealing with here?

332
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:18,625
Glad you're all caught up.

333
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:20,166
Then that means...

334
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:23,041
If our marriage got annulled,
what does that make us?

335
00:17:23,125 --> 00:17:25,916
Uh. Friends, I guess?

336
00:17:28,291 --> 00:17:30,458
That can't be.

337
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:36,458
Um... if you and I aren't
a couple anymore...

338
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:40,083
...does that mean
you don't want this?

339
00:17:40,166 --> 00:17:41,500
[HIDEKI]
Whoa!

340
00:17:41,583 --> 00:17:42,666
[AKO] I don't really understand
what you've been up to

341
00:17:42,750 --> 00:17:44,250
the last couple of days,

342
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:46,541
but I know that you've
been working extra hard.

343
00:17:46,625 --> 00:17:48,416
I wanted to make
something for you.

344
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:51,125
I was wondering what I'd do for
lunch, and then you showed up!

345
00:17:51,208 --> 00:17:52,666
Thanks, Ako!

346
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:55,875
Yeah, after I eat this, I'll be
ready for the home stretch!

347
00:17:55,958 --> 00:17:59,916
Rusian, I'm proud of you
for working so hard,

348
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,958
but try not to overdo it.

349
00:18:02,041 --> 00:18:04,416
Because the most
important thing to me

350
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:06,833
is making you happy.

351
00:18:08,625 --> 00:18:10,333
Ako, of all the random,

352
00:18:10,416 --> 00:18:12,500
sometimes inappropriate
things you've said to me,

353
00:18:12,583 --> 00:18:14,791
that was the most wife-like.

354
00:18:24,375 --> 00:18:27,750
[LON] "The Wannabe
Famous Swindler's Blog."

355
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:29,333
Get an email from someone

356
00:18:29,416 --> 00:18:31,375
claiming to have found a blog
that's even better than mine,

357
00:18:31,458 --> 00:18:34,291
so I take a peek to see
what all the fuss is about,

358
00:18:34,375 --> 00:18:37,416
and this cheap
knock-off's all I find?

359
00:18:37,500 --> 00:18:40,625
"From scamming Nekohime's Elite
Guard for fake membership dues

360
00:18:40,708 --> 00:18:42,125
to conning the
Black Magician out of

361
00:18:42,208 --> 00:18:45,208
a bundle of top-tier
purple items."

362
00:18:45,291 --> 00:18:48,333
Pretty impressive, kid.

363
00:18:48,416 --> 00:18:51,291
There's even a trading board.

364
00:18:51,375 --> 00:18:54,375
"Seeking RMTs in <i>LA</i> ," huh?

365
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:04,041
[LON]
These rates aren't half bad.

366
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:12,750
It's almost that time.
Is everything ready?

367
00:19:12,833 --> 00:19:13,833
Affirmative.

368
00:19:13,916 --> 00:19:14,916
[KYOH]
All right.

369
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,166
Let's get it on!

370
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:17,333
Roger!

371
00:19:25,333 --> 00:19:27,583
Target is confirmed.

372
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:30,541
[AKANE]
The character's name is Shoko.

373
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:33,708
Shoko! That's even more
ridiculous than Lon!

374
00:19:35,500 --> 00:19:39,333
Mission proceeding to
Phase Two. Commence Plan N!

375
00:19:39,416 --> 00:19:40,833
Roger that!

376
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:48,083
He's in. How are we?

377
00:19:48,166 --> 00:19:52,708
Waiting for the admins to
respond. Another 30 seconds.

378
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,166
Master, how long?

379
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:55,666
Just 15 seconds.

380
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:57,833
[HIDEKI]
He's getting impatient.

381
00:19:57,916 --> 00:20:00,000
Hold on. A little longer.

382
00:20:00,083 --> 00:20:01,958
Almost there.

383
00:20:02,041 --> 00:20:03,625
Okay, here they come!

384
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:12,583
[NYACK] Greetings,
I am Game Master Nyack.

385
00:20:12,666 --> 00:20:15,000
Tell me, do you know
why the two of you

386
00:20:15,083 --> 00:20:18,208
were teleported to
this location?

387
00:20:18,291 --> 00:20:20,333
The admins received a tip.

388
00:20:20,416 --> 00:20:23,541
We were told you were engaging
in Real Money Transactions.

389
00:20:23,625 --> 00:20:25,333
Is there any truth to this?

390
00:20:25,416 --> 00:20:26,166
What do you mean?

391
00:20:26,250 --> 00:20:29,166
Yes, that is accurate.

392
00:20:29,250 --> 00:20:31,625
This person contacted
me on a trading board

393
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:34,750
and negotiated
an RMT with me.

394
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:38,250
Bastard! You set me up,
didn't you?

395
00:20:38,333 --> 00:20:42,583
Haven't you ever heard that
turnabout is fair play?

396
00:20:42,666 --> 00:20:43,958
So what?

397
00:20:44,041 --> 00:20:46,500
Have we met before or somethin'?

398
00:20:50,625 --> 00:20:51,875
None of this matters

399
00:20:51,958 --> 00:20:54,208
because an RMT where no
money even exchanged hands

400
00:20:54,291 --> 00:20:55,791
doesn't prove anything.

401
00:20:55,875 --> 00:20:59,125
At most, we're looking at a
one week lockout, aren't we?

402
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:01,333
Not quite. One more thing.

403
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:03,208
You have been accused
of account hacking

404
00:21:03,291 --> 00:21:05,333
via the character
known as Rontan.

405
00:21:05,416 --> 00:21:07,916
Rontan? Who cares about him?

406
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,166
[NYACK] Based on the IP
information submitted to us

407
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:13,416
by the trading board,
we have proof.

408
00:21:13,500 --> 00:21:16,791
You have committed several
access violations.

409
00:21:16,875 --> 00:21:19,166
We are considering
filing charges.

410
00:21:19,250 --> 00:21:21,250
You can't intimidate
me, Blondie!

411
00:21:21,333 --> 00:21:22,708
There's no way a site that dirty

412
00:21:22,791 --> 00:21:25,041
would ever hand any
IPs over to an admin!

413
00:21:25,125 --> 00:21:27,208
Exactly what we wanted
you to think.

414
00:21:27,291 --> 00:21:28,208
[SHOKO]
Huh?

415
00:21:28,291 --> 00:21:29,708
[RUSIAN]
It was my website.

416
00:21:29,791 --> 00:21:31,541
I put the whole thing
up three days ago.

417
00:21:31,625 --> 00:21:33,166
Dude, are you kidding me?

418
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:35,291
That site has posts that go
back for a couple years!

419
00:21:35,375 --> 00:21:37,166
[RUSIAN]
Oh man, you're tellin' me!

420
00:21:37,250 --> 00:21:39,625
Fabricating a few years' worth
of authentic-sounding posts

421
00:21:39,708 --> 00:21:40,875
really takes it outta ya!

422
00:21:40,958 --> 00:21:44,041
No way. You're bluffing.

423
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:46,833
You faked multiple years
worth of blog material

424
00:21:46,916 --> 00:21:48,833
just to set me up?

425
00:21:48,916 --> 00:21:50,500
[RUSIAN]
Heh.

426
00:21:50,583 --> 00:21:52,000
Are you some kinda idiot?

427
00:21:52,083 --> 00:21:54,666
You wasted that much of your
time to trick one person?

428
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,083
Damn straight.

429
00:21:56,166 --> 00:21:59,916
Besides... you made my wife cry.

430
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:03,291
You better believe I was
going to make you pay!

431
00:22:04,458 --> 00:22:06,166
[AKO]
You guys made a fake blog?

432
00:22:06,250 --> 00:22:07,583
Is that why you've
all been staying up

433
00:22:07,666 --> 00:22:09,291
to work the last few nights?

434
00:22:09,375 --> 00:22:11,625
Yeah. And watching the hacker.

435
00:22:11,708 --> 00:22:14,125
We logged him replying to
the trade request from home,

436
00:22:14,208 --> 00:22:15,708
unaware of our trap.

437
00:22:15,791 --> 00:22:18,750
[AKANE] Then, he showed up for
the deal as the character Shoko.

438
00:22:18,833 --> 00:22:21,125
[HIDEKI] Whenever he got up to
anything not entirely legal,

439
00:22:21,208 --> 00:22:23,875
he was careful to use
a separate IP.

440
00:22:23,958 --> 00:22:26,458
Including, of course,
when he hacked my account.

441
00:22:26,541 --> 00:22:28,291
The admins have been proactive.

442
00:22:28,375 --> 00:22:30,750
Rusian-- No, Piroshki's account

443
00:22:30,833 --> 00:22:32,333
has been locked out
for three days,

444
00:22:32,416 --> 00:22:34,541
suspended for an attempted RMT.

445
00:22:34,625 --> 00:22:37,750
Yeah, but I was prepared for
a much stricter punishment.

446
00:22:37,833 --> 00:22:40,000
[AKANE] You guys failed to
mention the very best part!

447
00:22:40,083 --> 00:22:42,666
The admins also restored
Rusian's character!

448
00:22:42,750 --> 00:22:45,041
Yay! Yay! Yay! Yay!

449
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:47,708
[sighs] Nyack is
a total dreamboat.

450
00:22:47,791 --> 00:22:49,500
So does that mean I
finally get to have

451
00:22:49,583 --> 00:22:51,250
my dear Rusian back with me?

452
00:22:51,333 --> 00:22:54,083
All's well that ends
well, right guys?

453
00:22:54,166 --> 00:22:58,416
No. I'm afraid we still have
some unfinished business.

454
00:23:35,708 --> 00:23:38,916
Ako, it's a bit late
to bring this up,

455
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:42,791
but when my account was hacked,
I was honestly shocked.

456
00:23:42,875 --> 00:23:46,875
Having someone else logged in as
Rusian, I just felt so helpless,

457
00:23:46,958 --> 00:23:50,541
so scared I would lose you too.

458
00:23:50,625 --> 00:23:53,333
I don't ever wanna go through
something like that again.

459
00:23:53,416 --> 00:23:57,166
I want-- I want to be closer
to you than I was before.

460
00:23:57,250 --> 00:23:58,958
So, uh...

461
00:23:59,041 --> 00:24:00,916
Would you like Rusian
a little less,

462
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,458
and try to like the real life
Hideki a little bit more?

463
00:24:10,166 --> 00:24:11,958
I can't.

464
00:24:12,041 --> 00:24:15,208
Sorry, I can't like you anymore.

465
00:24:15,291 --> 00:24:18,958
Because I already love you
with all of my heart!

466
00:24:31,541 --> 00:24:33,583
[KYOH] I came up with a
fool-proof anti-hacking measure.

467
00:24:33,666 --> 00:24:34,750
[HIDEKI]
What is it?

468
00:24:34,833 --> 00:24:35,583
[KYOH] We just buy
out the entire hotel!

469
00:24:35,666 --> 00:24:36,625
[HIDEKI]
You can't!

470
00:24:36,708 --> 00:24:37,666
[KYOH]
Fine, we'll buy the servers.

471
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:38,708
[HIDEKI]
As if!

472
00:24:38,791 --> 00:24:39,625
[KYOH]
Even better, the admin team!

473
00:24:39,708 --> 00:24:40,958
[HIDEKI]
Get serious!

